  "text": "Cremer and colleagues [CITATION_1] discussed several potential mechanisms for early bioprosthetic valve failure based on operative and echocardiographic findings, and proposed a widened differential diagnosis including thrombosis (BPVT), pannus formation, early structural valve deterioration (SVD), endocarditis, patient prosthesis mismatch, and technical error.",
